User: Write an applescript file that will log the frontmost window that I am viewing. Return the app display name. Assume I already have a MacBook and can excute this using oascripts. Write only the code.
Gemini:
tell application "System Events"
    set frontApp to first application process whose frontmost is true
    set appName to displayed name of frontApp
end tell
return appName
User: Write an applescript file that will record the total number of tabs on Chrome I have opened and the current URL of the active window. Return the data as a dictionary and have the script be able to be called from command line oascript command.
Gemini:
tell application "Google Chrome"
    set activeURL to URL of active tab of front window
    set totalTabs to 0
    set allWindows to every window
    repeat with aWindow in allWindows
        set totalTabs to totalTabs + (count of tabs of aWindow)
    end repeat
    return {activeURL, totalTabs}
end tell
